headline.print_headline: Maine Baby Lobster Decline Could End High Catches
headline.main: Maine Baby Lobster Decline Could End High Catches

lead_paragraph: The number of baby lobsters settling off the rocky coast of Maine continues to steadily decline — possibly foreshadowing an end to the recent record catches that have boosted New England's lobster fishery, scientists say.
